	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 24th 7:36 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a level 20 druid...I have all the recommended spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;I don't understand the popularity of the kiting concept.  For me, this is what happens.  a)  I root or snare, b)  I start putting DoTs on it (which at this point is stinging swarm, which only takes off about 115 in 60 seconds).  If it breaks out of the snare or root (Which happens often), the time I use to med does not recoup me enough mana in order to make it worthwhile.  Usually, the creature comes and whacks me, at which point, I lose some health.  c)  repeating the DoT...fine, except I run out of mana fast (I am a half-elf druid, so that explains part of the problem).  I end up meleeing 80% of the time, and don't do too badly (especially with a good weapon, and some decent blunt/slashing skills).  Perhaps at some point, I may not be able to melee as effectively, but despite contrary belief, a druid can solo fine until at least 20.  I plan to continue this road for a while anyway.<br><br>Here's part of the problem:  at level 19-20, I still don't kill enough things that drop plat.  To afford the big wisdom-enhancing items, you need a lot of plat.  I don't have that, and as a result, my mana supply suffers.  Initially, when I set up my character, the most points I could allocate to it for wisdom was maxxed out at 95.  With some slight wisdom gear, I am at 106 right now.  Not sure where people get the 140-160 range from at this level, but they obviously are wearing some darn good gear.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97447901330393></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97447901330393><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=97447901330393>RE: Kiting...overrated?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=97447901330393#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 17th 11:36 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, i have a lvl 28 druid on the e'ci server with wiz of 108, here is how i kite. 1)cast dmg shield on me (shield of barbs) 2)sight in mob and snare. 3)cast dot (swarm at lo lvls, Crud at 24) 3)then mana dump the careless lightning and dizzying wind until i have one bub of mana left (aprox 4to5 sucessfull casts. by this time the dot has worn off. 4)recast dot on mob and snare again (at this point im oom) usually by this time the mob has started running, but because of snare they dont move or attack,(dont root or they will still attack) 5) melee till it dies,usually the dot will finish it off. I REPEAT---ALL OF THIS IS DONE WITH A WIZ OF 108. most of the time i never get hit by mob at all. but cast the dmg shield just in case. I have been doing this since lvl 23 in lake of ill omen. Saranaks recruits and goblin warriors, these mobs have been droping 2 to 3 pp. I can easily solo by kiting for much more exp and loot than group hunting. Thats my take on kiting, If anyone who reads this is on E'ci my char name is Negluas, and i would be happy to demonstrate technique. HAVE FUN<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
