	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, I love to partner up with druids. Once they get track its a blast. They track something then i tashani it FIRST, so snare less likely to be resisted. They snare and keep snareing if it is resisted. Usually, if it is resisted which is not too often, it take 3 times to succesfully snare it. We both ping-pong it with dd's and stuff and NEVER get hit. It's dead before snare wears off and we still have AT LEAST half mana. I have successfully taken on reds with a druid and got great exp. Also, If more mobs come into play, i can mez it/ mem blur(if not a aggro mob) we can run away from LoS and we are fine. This might be just my luck but try it. Kitting is great! Also for you non-druids reverse kiting works good too, but we'll not go into that yet. =)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Laleini Windsong <br>Enchantress Extroadinare</td></tr>
