	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp; One thing to remember is the DoT kite nerf- DoT's now do 66% (i think) damage if you are moving away from the MoB (Fear kiting still works GREAT though). When soloing I almost exclusively DD kite till the mob is low, then re-snare if necessary, Dmg Sheild, DoT and melee.<br><br>   Your wisdom is a weak point. Start hunting well known money makers, even if the exp isnt too hot. You NEED to get some +wis items.  <br>   <br>   If you get tired of Lavastorm then you may want to camp the Dark Elf guard right by the Nektulos Lavastorm entrance. Be sure to pull him towards Lavastorm when he gets low on health as he will draw a few stone golems if he gets past that rock he spawns by. The DE guard drops a bronze sword every time that sells to the gypsies in Lava for 2pp 5gp at my 75 Charisma. <br><br>   Another optionis not to solo. Its very debatable as to which yeilds more exp. But to me there is no questioning which is more fun. I solo quite a bit, but theres nothing like fear kiting with a necro. Our DoT's stack and the downtime is so short theres no way that soloing can beat it. Only bad thing is having to split the loot, but if you're not broke then its worth it. <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
