	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am a 45 Druid on Karana and soloed most of the time to 45 in very short time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Kiting is absolutely essential for Druids who like to solo.  When you hit lvl 30 and beyond, if you attempt to melee, watch you hp bar fall to almost nothing in 5 sec flat.  I have been able to kite reds well into my 30's and multiple kited up to 6 blues at once for amazing xp.  There are so many variations of kiting I have learned and discovered, I encourage you to read up on them on all the sites.  Also, my wis was 135 through my 20's, 150 through my 30's, and for the most part 175 through 40's.  But if you think you can melee after 25, forget it and make a warrior, pally or sk, cause your Druid will do a lot of dying. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
